President of East Timor Supports Korea's Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 26 (KCNA) -- The government and people of East Timor will positively support reconciliation, cooperation and independent and peaceful reunification between the north and south of Korea based on the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.
 President of the Democratic Republic of East Timor Xanana Gusmao said this when he received credentials from new DPRK Ambassador Chon Jae Hong on November 21. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion the president wished the Korean people success in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is firmly defending the dignity and sovereignty of the country and the nation despite the ceaseless foreign pressure, the president said, adding that he would make all efforts to boost the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries in the interests of the two governments and the two peoples.

Government Authorities' Crackdown on Labour Movement Condemned in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 26 (KCNA) -- The "Federation of Korean Trade Unions" held a large rally condemning the government authorities' crackdown on the labour movement in Seoul on November 23, according to south Korean MBC and KBS.
 The rally was attended by more than 40,000 unionists under the organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the rally the organization strongly demanded that the authorities abolish discrimination against part-time jobs and permit the trade union of public service officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Korean Confederation of Trade Unions" held a rally with at least 200 unionists attending in Seoul on November 22 in demand of the settlement of the issue of part-time workers and an end to imposing damages on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 40 civic and public organizations including the Catholic Human Rights Committee held a rally for smashing the authorities' suppression of the labour movement on the same day and staged a demonstration up to Myongdong Cathedral.

Three Generals of Mt. Paektu Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 26 (KCNA) -- This year many foreign figures wrote and published books and poems in praise of the immortal feats performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu.
 Academician, Prof. and Dr. G. I. Korotkov, secretary general for academic studies of the Military History Institute, wrote the book "Victors" on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the Korean people's victory in the Korean war, deeply moved by the outstanding military idea and tactics of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sergei Lisitski, writer of the Russian Union of Writers, visited the DPRK and wrote the book "Story of DPRK", after avidly reading Kim Il Sung's Reminiscences "With the Century". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alexander Viktorvich Brezhnev, journalist of the Russian newspaper Zavtra, authored the book "Red Korea" in which he gave his impressions of the DPRK he visited in comparison with the realities of those countries where socialism collapsed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Javed Ansari, secretary general of the Society for the Study of Self-Reliance of Pakistan, wrote the book "Country of Eternal Sun". Printed in the book are a globe surrounded by 21 five-pointed stars and a photograph of leader Kim Jong Il in the centre of a star on top of the globe. By this he meant that Kim Jong Il is the sun of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the books recently sent to the DPRK are the book "Army of Korea" written by Marwan Sudah, chairman of the Arab Committee for Solidarity with the Korean People and Support to Korea's Reunification in Jordan, and the book "Korea, Beacon of the Times" written by Yehia Zakaria Khairallah, secretary general of the Arab Association for Arts, Culture and Information of Egypt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Takashi Nada, representative of the Japan, Ehime, Institute for Modern Korean Studies, wrote epic "Land of Victory" and Dipak Sharma, chairman of the Nepalese Young Poets' Forum, 5 poems including "Defender of Nation, Father of People". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Bangladeshi Journalist Shiraz Chowdry wrote the poem "In Memory of Mother Kim Jong Suk" praising the woman general of Mt. Paektu as an anti-Japanese war hero and mother of Korea.

Middle School Renamed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kanggye, November 25 (KCNA) -- Namsan Middle School in Kanggye City, Jagang Province, was renamed Hero Namsan Middle School.
 The school produced 2 DPRK heroes and 9 labour heroes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A renaming ceremony took place at the school yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony were Yon Hyong Muk, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Choe Ki Ryong, chairman of the Jagang Provincial People's Committee, officials concerned, teachers and students of the school and working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Kyong Nam, secretary of the Jagang Provincial Party Committee, made an address to be followed by speeches of Schoolmistress Kim Yong Suk, Labor hero Kim Yun Thae from the school and student Kwak Su Gyong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that 11 graduates from the school became heroes, speakers called on the teachers and students to learn from the distinguished spirit of devotedly defending the leader, do-or-die spirit and noble patriotism displayed by the heroes and uphold the Songun revolutionary leadership of the WPK with loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They underscored the need for the teaching staff to decisively raise their political and professional qualifications and strengthen the education of students to more successfully bring up more revolutionary intellectuals needed for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation of Juche. All the students of the school should fully prepare themselves as successor to the Juche revolutionary cause fully prepared mentally, morally and physically and revolutionaries of the younger generation in the Songun era, honored to study at the school of heroes, they declared.

Outbursts of U.S. Ambassador in S. Korea Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 26 (KCNA) -- Hubbard, U.S. ambassador in south Korea, a few days ago, stringed out the jargon that south Korea would set "an example", if it continued economic cooperation with north Korea while leaving the latter without restraining itself in the acts unacceptable to the U.S., and that "economic cooperation" should be done in a cautious manner to be "bilateral cooperation beneficial to both."
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hubbard meddled in inter-Korean cooperation and talked this or that as if he were an "inspector." This was an impudent behavior without discretion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His outbursts cannot be construed otherwise than an aggressive one interfering in other's internal affairs in pursuit of a very sinister purpose to throw a wet blanket over and totally spoil inter-Korean economic cooperation now running a smooth course, the commentary says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His outcries for "cautious" economic cooperation with the north were, in fact, a certain pressure upon south Korea to stop it and go back to confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Inter-Korean economic cooperation is a patriotic undertaking for the north and the south to promote common interests of the Korean nation in the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration. But Hubbard put his nose into inter-Korean economic cooperation in an attempt to bar it, behaving himself as the "governor general" of a U.S. colony. This has touched off the towering rage of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to give up its unreasonable interference in the inter-Korean economic cooperation, well aware of the will and aspiration of the Korean nation.

Japan Urged to Compensate for Its Human Rights Abuses 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 26 (KCNA) -- Recently the list of 427,129 Korean victims who were forcibly drafted during the Japanese imperialists' military occupation of Korea was made public. In this regard, voices strongly demanding the Japanese authorities make apology and compensation to the victims and their bereaved families are growing louder day by day.
 "We can never die before the punishment of the crimes of the Japanese imperialists before the world's conscience and thorough compensation from them and we will get the price of blood paid by Japan at any cost." This is the unshakable will of the victims and their kinsmen and friends. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The forcible drafting and massacres committed by the Japanese imperialists were grave human rights abuses they openly committed as a state policy, disregarding international justice and morality and violating international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In fact, the recently published list of the victims to forcible drafting is only the tip of the iceberg in light of the hideous crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists. The claim of the victims to human rights abuses and their bereaved families to compensation fully conforms with the universal definition of human rights and the principle of international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is too natural that the DPRK proposed to Japan to hold inter-governmental talks between the two countries at an early date to discuss the issue of compensation to the victims to human rights abuses who have been surveyed and confirmed so far as this reflects the trend of the times. 
 The Japanese authorities should look straight into the trend of the times and, in consonance with it, respond as soon as possible to the inter-governmental talks for discussing the issue of compensation for the human rights abuses committed by the Japanese imperialists against the Korean people in the past.

Fish Breeding Proves Successful in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 26 (KCNA) -- Great efforts have been channeled into fish farming in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 A fish farm covering some 230 hectares was built in Nampho City and the Taegwan and Unsan catfish farms in North Phyongan Province in October. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many fish farms have been built across the country in recent years. Among them are the Onchon Fish Farm, Yonggwang Youth Fish Farm, Songhwa Catfish Farm and Pyongyang Catfish Farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Yonggwang Youth Fish Farm in South Hamgyong Province is breeding freshwater fishes in a scientific and technical way in more than 60 ponds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fish farms in North Phyongan Province are raising saltwater fishes as well as freshwater fishes to suit the conditions of the tideland on the West Coast. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The lowland and mountain areas such as South and North Hwanghae and Jagang provinces have based their fish farming on natural feed and scientific and technical processing of feed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Modern catfish farms in various areas including Pyongyang, Samchon County of South Hwanghae Province and Tongsin County of Jagang Province supply hundreds of tons of fish to the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, fish breeding farms and spawning ponds throughout the country fully supply fries to the fish and catfish farms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government is planning to build fish farms with an area of 20-30 hectares in each city and county.
